race.comment: LADY COCO (5) finished 1.3L off the winner here two back before a 0.8L defeat most recently after jumping the race favourite. She's on the quick turnaround again today and the wide draw doesn't hurt too much as she tends to get back anyway. Rates highly on recent efforts and can land the knockout blow. EXCEED THE BOOM (2) is better than we've seen in his past couple when racing over further and getting back to a sprint trip today can see him improve. He had excuses when beaten as favourite last start and he can make an impression in his stable debut. NONEOFYOURBUSINESS (11) will find this a little easier than the maiden's she's been racing in. Whiting hops in the saddle this time around and she remains down in the weights. Looks well placed this time around and can be there at the finish. TANGO RHYTHM (9) is better than she showed first-up and is not to be discounted. BLINDING LUCK (12) can bounce back with the rise in trip suiting.
